{"text": "same rotation angle (\n\n) is deduced from the \"Berry phases\" of the \"up\" and \"down\" polarizations. Below we provide\n\ndetails on methods (a-e).\n\n(a) Projection method.{ We divide the trajectory r(t) into small in\n\nnitesimal steps. In each step the arrow is\n\nparallel transported in the simple-minded Euclidean sense, but then it is projected back to the tangent direction.\n\nNote that the shortening of the length is second order in the step size, hence the arrows keeps its length in the limit\n\nof a continuous process.\n\n(b) Tangent plane method.{ At each point along the trajectory r(t) we attach a \rat piece of tangent plane. For\n\n109\n\nexample, if we move along a line of constant latitude the union of all these pieces is a conical surface. This surface\n\ncan be regarded as \rat, and we can perform on it an Euclidean \"parallel transport\". See left panels of the\n\ngure\n\n[N.P.Ong website].\n\n(c) Geodesic walk method.{ We can always approximated r(t) as a sum of in\n\nnitesimal geodesic steps. In the\n\ncase of a sphere \"geodesic\" means to go along a big circle. The law of \"parallel transport\" is simple: the arrow should\n\nkeep\n\nxed angle with the geodesic. See right panel of the\n\ngure [N.Manini website].\n\n(d) Metric connection method.{ To each point r= (x1;x2) on the surface we attach a set of \"unit vectors\" with\n\nwhich a metric is associated:\n\n\u0000 !en=@nr=@r\n\n@xn; g nm=h\u0000 !enj\u0000 !emi=h@nrj@mri (22.2)\n\nThen we can de\n\nne so called \"connection\" , that can be derived from the metric:\n\n\u0000n;km =h\u0000 !enj@k\u0000 !emi=h@nrj@k@mri=1\n\n2[@kgnm+@mgkn\u0000@ngkm] (22.3)\n\nThe metric connection allows us to calculate full derivatives:\n\njvi=X\n\nnvnj\u0000 !eni; D kjvi=X\n\nn\"\n\n@kvn+X\n\nm\u0000n;kmvm#\n\nj\u0000 !eni (22.4)\n\nThe construct D=@+ \u0000 is known as the \"covariant derivative\". It takes into account the explicit variation of the\n\nvector-components as well as the implicit parametric variation of the basis-vectors.", "embedding": [0.014387494, 0.03634204, 0.0083431685, -0.030286578, 0.002681394, 0.012882281, 0.0015788347, -0.01502125, 0.0059106997, 0.09328101, 0.019886691, 0.00639099, 0.0025672538, -0.043859232, -0.02448355, 0.045978706, -0.0069093434, -0.027005797, -0.0383, 0.0007334362, 0.046132147, 0.020914491, -0.06776062, -0.028509252, 0.011834542, 0.017702406, 0.049830314, -0.009612029, 0.06307635, 0.062060382, 0.036051784, -0.01050913, -0.004379623, -0.035385832, -0.006315346, -0.007434152, 0.026175072, -0.03252425, 0.028306281, -0.008034936, 0.034120888, 0.008105219, -0.011397784, -0.0044049234, -0.036837697, -0.01646332, -0.0053971144, -0.03297261, -0.012989008, -0.043210357, 0.0021555575, 0.023397677, 0.025864165, -0.009495712, -0.013656883, -0.015169764, 0.026669985, 0.023251675, -0.016206585, 0.036654755, 0.00187932, 0.011052546, -0.033665106, -0.0698733, 0.008639225, 0.04499739, -0.012607936, 0.022906665, -0.03091439, -0.04988799, -0.06771319, -0.00016029629, 0.021311225, 0.008366966, -0.026917696, 0.052902043, -0.00942068, -0.011441073, -0.010545371, 0.019623943, -0.01134258, -0.0033065204, -0.05819077, 0.048090152, -0.0076949606, 0.0059549944, 0.008368261, 0.015343299, 0.019519746, -0.015548555, -0.007569528, 0.045912556, -0.02365304, -0.00865088, 0.015488712, -0.0021406126, -0.040809166, 0.03894699, 0.046247385, 0.017612912, 0.011016952, 0.08068275, -0.011608636, 0.029116228, -0.007768924, 0.06618978, -0.0017121445, -0.0030186092, -0.014200384, -0.027443342, 0.0143456105, -0.023791252, 0.013153093, 0.026505603, 0.002098716, 0.032547917, 0.00078380643, -0.0049450123, -0.01152347, -0.0020413145, 0.0061607393, -0.007947168, 0.04260167, 0.032127094, 0.021081991, -0.035837904, 0.0017298289, 0.010386607, -0.07829288, -0.0074340766, 0.027070351, -0.035166446, -0.017251141, 0.007399334, -0.013266349, 0.026255889, -0.029698541, 0.005434265, 0.0026067607, -0.01586787, 0.016489437, -0.020915322, 0.033129245, 0.06811117, 0.012377572